<section anchor="introduction">
      <name>Introduction</name>
      <t>Lightning talks are brief presentations, typically lasting 5 minutes,
that deliver focused insights on a specific topic <xref target="WIKI"/>. This RFC proposes a
structure for such talks to optimize clarity and audience engagement.</t>
    </section>
    <section anchor="structure">
      <name>Structure</name>
      <t>There is no structure.</t>
    </section>
    <section anchor="considerations">
      <name>Considerations</name>
      <ul spacing="normal">
        <li>
          <t>Ensure talk fits within the 5 minutes.</t>
        </li>
        <li>
          <t>Avoid sales pitchs.</t>
        </li>
        <li>
          <t>Make sure your talks fits the code of conduct.</t>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
